The paper deals with lower bounds on graph compression schemes, specifically additive spanners, emulators, and shortcut sets. This falls under the category of graph algorithms and data structures, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also involves geometric arguments, as well as analysis of graph properties such as diameter, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CG (computational geometry) and cs.NA (numerical analysis). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial arguments and lower bounds, which could place it under cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.GT (graph theory).
